1
00:01:50,060 --> 00:01:54,360
<i>Do you have what it takes to stop me?</i>

2
00:01:58,860 --> 00:02:00,070
Just as

3
00:02:00,950 --> 00:02:02,740
Askeladd did back then?

4
00:02:06,660 --> 00:02:08,160
Please leave, Thorfinn.

5
00:02:09,750 --> 00:02:13,380
You're a strange guy,
but I don't want to kill you.

6
00:02:18,130 --> 00:02:20,930
This is how the world works.

7
00:02:21,510 --> 00:02:25,100
In the end, whoever has more power
always gets their way.

8
00:02:27,730 --> 00:02:29,390
Damn Vikings…

9
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:40,700
How foolish of you, my son.

10
00:02:41,570 --> 00:02:44,530
You're still hesitant of becoming
a full-fledged king?

11
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:49,540
Why did you reveal your honest feelings

12
00:02:49,620 --> 00:02:52,920
to such lowly people?

13
00:02:55,840 --> 00:03:01,590
I hope you didn't think that
you could possibly understand each other.

14
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:06,510
They are a pitiful flock of sheep.

15
00:03:07,930 --> 00:03:11,940
You are a lone shepherd.

16
00:03:12,020 --> 00:03:17,030
You raise them, cull them, and skin them.

17
00:03:17,860 --> 00:03:23,950
The work of a shepherd
cannot be understood by the sheep.

18
00:03:24,660 --> 00:03:27,580
You rule over them,
that's all there is to it.

19
00:03:28,290 --> 00:03:32,330
That is the best thing
you can do for the sheep.

20
00:03:34,170 --> 00:03:35,540
Canute…

21
00:03:39,590 --> 00:03:44,720
If you intend to use your authority
to forcefully get your way…

22
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:46,100
Kill him.

23
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:49,350
That man is a threat.

24
00:03:50,270 --> 00:03:53,520
One sheep can confuse the flock

25
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:57,270
and send them running off a precipice.

26
00:03:58,730 --> 00:03:59,610
I will…

27
00:04:00,190 --> 00:04:01,190
Kill him.

28
00:04:02,320 --> 00:04:05,110
Fulfill your duty as the king.

29
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:06,990
I will…

30
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:14,000
run.

31
00:04:33,350 --> 00:04:34,440
Run?

32
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:36,730
That's it?

33
00:04:42,110 --> 00:04:43,280
That's all?

34
00:04:46,570 --> 00:04:48,320
What else can I do?

35
00:04:49,490 --> 00:04:52,410
Do you want us to kill
each other here or what?

36
00:04:57,460 --> 00:04:59,630
The paradise you speak of

37
00:05:00,630 --> 00:05:02,590
saves the majority

38
00:05:02,670 --> 00:05:04,760
and oppresses a few.

39
00:05:05,380 --> 00:05:07,680
That's the way it is, right?

40
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:12,930
I can't say if that is good or bad.

41
00:05:13,730 --> 00:05:16,440
And I have no right to condemn
your recklessness.

42
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:21,610
So I have no choice but to run away.

43
00:05:23,070 --> 00:05:25,150
-Einar, let's go.
-You are excellent.

44
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,990
As a warrior.

45
00:05:27,070 --> 00:05:28,660
You must have other options.

46
00:05:29,450 --> 00:05:30,780
Did you

47
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:35,250
appear before the emperor

48
00:05:35,330 --> 00:05:37,460
just to admonish me?

49
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:39,960
You got your face swollen for that?

50
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:43,590
And it was all a waste.

51
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:46,920
Goodbye,

52
00:05:47,550 --> 00:05:48,840
Your Majesty.

53
00:06:30,010 --> 00:06:30,840
So many…

54
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:34,680
So many people want to bargain with me.

55
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:37,810
Some even try to set me up.

56
00:06:39,230 --> 00:06:40,350
But…

57
00:06:42,230 --> 00:06:43,980
What is up with you?

58
00:06:44,730 --> 00:06:46,320
You are such an idiot!

59
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:50,320
You have nothing up your sleeve?

60
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:53,950
You came here completely unarmed
and you got beaten to a pulp

61
00:06:54,030 --> 00:06:57,290
just to tell me to stop seizing this farm?

62
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:03,580
Is it that funny?

63
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:05,590
It is.

64
00:07:06,210 --> 00:07:09,630
This is the stupidest peace negotiation
I've ever experienced.

65
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:20,480
You're going to run, huh?

66
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:25,570
Yeah.

67
00:07:30,490 --> 00:07:32,990
<i>Someone like him</i>

68
00:07:33,070 --> 00:07:35,620
<i>can come from Vikings, huh?</i>

69
00:07:36,740 --> 00:07:38,490
<i>What a beautiful man.</i>

70
00:07:45,710 --> 00:07:47,670
You will turn your back on conflict.

71
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:49,010
Then run to where?

72
00:07:50,260 --> 00:07:52,050
Somewhere other than here.

73
00:07:53,010 --> 00:07:55,550
I can't tell you about it.

74
00:07:58,260 --> 00:08:01,100
My territory is constantly expanding.

75
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:03,350
In time,

76
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:05,610
my authority may reach there too.

77
00:08:08,070 --> 00:08:10,280
I'll keep running as long as I can.

78
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:13,110
As long as there is a place to run to,

79
00:08:13,700 --> 00:08:15,280
I will not fight.

80
00:08:17,410 --> 00:08:19,660
<i>I will build a land of peace</i>

81
00:08:20,410 --> 00:08:22,330
<i>in a place out of the king's reach,</i>

82
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:25,080
<i>using an approach different from you.</i>

83
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,710
For the people who cannot

84
00:08:29,460 --> 00:08:31,420
live in the world you create.

85
00:08:32,920 --> 00:08:36,550
For your sake, and my sake as well.

86
00:08:40,010 --> 00:08:42,850
Are you saying
that you will fill in the gaps

87
00:08:42,930 --> 00:08:44,980
that my project can't fill?

88
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:49,480
Are you capable of that?

89
00:08:51,570 --> 00:08:56,110
My power
is much smaller compared to yours.

90
00:08:56,660 --> 00:08:58,950
I can't handle a gap that is too big.

91
00:09:00,370 --> 00:09:03,870
<i>If you continue</i>
<i>to persecute people like this,</i>

92
00:09:04,410 --> 00:09:08,040
<i>nobody will be able to help you anymore.</i>

93
00:09:11,340 --> 00:09:13,090
So you better try your best too.

94
00:09:13,710 --> 00:09:15,970
Don't give me more work to do.

95
00:09:21,390 --> 00:09:22,560
My goodness…

96
00:09:23,180 --> 00:09:26,100
You really learned how to use your words.

97
00:09:27,690 --> 00:09:30,900
I wonder who you got that from.

98
00:09:46,250 --> 00:09:47,540
Interesting.

99
00:09:48,330 --> 00:09:51,960
This is the most difficult
peace negotiation I've ever experienced.

100
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:02,510
What… in… the world?

101
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:06,020
Even the ships are gone?

102
00:10:06,850 --> 00:10:09,600
Where did you go, King Canute?

103
00:10:09,690 --> 00:10:11,270
This is ridiculous!

104
00:10:12,940 --> 00:10:18,110
We still haven't settled this!

105
00:10:23,450 --> 00:10:27,410
Floki was grumbling.

106
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:30,420
He can't comprehend why
we're withdrawing from the farm.

107
00:10:32,590 --> 00:10:35,170
Are you also unhappy about it, Wulf?

108
00:10:37,010 --> 00:10:38,130
Not at all.

109
00:10:40,260 --> 00:10:43,890
I will call off our plans
of requisitioning other farms as well.

110
00:10:44,760 --> 00:10:47,810
I'd feel bad if I gave
Thorfinn more work to do.

111
00:10:59,990 --> 00:11:01,360
Up until now,

112
00:11:02,410 --> 00:11:04,030
I thought you were the only one

113
00:11:04,620 --> 00:11:06,740
who was fighting alongside me.

114
00:11:08,410 --> 00:11:10,120
But today,

115
00:11:11,290 --> 00:11:13,080
I found a new comrade.

116
00:11:26,180 --> 00:11:28,350
<i>After this, Canute</i>

117
00:11:28,430 --> 00:11:31,100
<i>disbanded the Danish troops that were</i>

118
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:34,860
<i>stationed in England and proving to be</i>
<i>a financial burden.</i>

119
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:42,950
<i>Ultimately,</i>
<i>Canute's personal force of Danish troops</i>

120
00:11:43,490 --> 00:11:47,030
<i>was reduced to one fleet of just 16 ships.</i>

121
00:11:52,750 --> 00:11:56,750
<i>However, they did not face</i>
<i>any rebellions within England</i>

122
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:58,460
<i>like they anticipated.</i>

123
00:12:00,590 --> 00:12:03,800
<i>Because Canute relinquished</i>
<i>military power,</i>

124
00:12:03,880 --> 00:12:07,810
<i>the peers of England</i>
<i>came to see Canute's trust.</i>

125
00:12:09,350 --> 00:12:12,810
<i>The relationship between</i>
<i>the conqueror and the conquered</i>

126
00:12:12,890 --> 00:12:14,810
<i>was starting to change.</i>

127
00:12:32,500 --> 00:12:33,870
It feels good.

128
00:13:56,160 --> 00:13:58,080
As long as you're alive…

129
00:13:59,330 --> 00:14:00,380
you can start again…

130
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:10,010
Why do I have to live?

131
00:14:29,030 --> 00:14:30,160
Thorfinn…

132
00:14:31,990 --> 00:14:34,740
-You're all better now?
-Yeah.

133
00:14:35,790 --> 00:14:37,870
I'm still a little wobbly,

134
00:14:38,790 --> 00:14:39,790
but I'm okay.

135
00:14:44,090 --> 00:14:46,710
Stop being so reckless.

136
00:14:48,340 --> 00:14:49,380
Sorry.

137
00:15:02,190 --> 00:15:04,610
Are you going, Thorfinn?

138
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:08,740
To a land on the other side of the sea?

139
00:15:13,030 --> 00:15:14,370
It's Vinland.

140
00:15:16,870 --> 00:15:18,250
Vinland…

141
00:15:22,630 --> 00:15:23,750
At that moment,

142
00:15:24,790 --> 00:15:26,550
when Arnheid

143
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:29,210
took her last breath,

144
00:15:30,510 --> 00:15:33,140
I couldn't give an answer right away.

145
00:15:34,930 --> 00:15:35,970
Why

146
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:38,680
do they have to live?

147
00:15:40,140 --> 00:15:41,440
These souls

148
00:15:42,140 --> 00:15:44,860
live through hell and seek peace in death.

149
00:15:46,610 --> 00:15:49,490
What can you possibly say to them?

150
00:15:56,950 --> 00:15:59,540
I want a world where we can
tell them to live.

151
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:04,630
A place where we can confidently
say that to people who don't have

152
00:16:05,880 --> 00:16:07,420
any escape other than death.

153
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:11,970
A place that overshadows
the appeal of death.

154
00:16:15,760 --> 00:16:18,010
I want that in our world.

155
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:21,390
That is all…

156
00:16:21,980 --> 00:16:25,730
That is all we ever wanted.

157
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:49,250
I can't back down.

158
00:16:53,220 --> 00:16:55,590
If it doesn't exist…

159
00:17:00,310 --> 00:17:02,770
If it's not there, I'll make it.

160
00:17:07,600 --> 00:17:08,730
Einar…

161
00:17:16,490 --> 00:17:19,160
Come with me, my brother.

162
00:17:20,120 --> 00:17:23,410
We're going to make
a land of peace in Vinland.

163
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:27,290
Somewhere we can proudly
tell Arnheid about.

164
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:33,130
Let's do it, my brother.
Let's go to the other side of the sea

165
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:36,630
and create a land
where there are no slaves or war.

166
00:17:42,260 --> 00:17:44,480
For Arnheid.

167
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:32,610
Are you sure

168
00:18:33,570 --> 00:18:34,980
you're okay with this?

169
00:18:36,570 --> 00:18:40,360
It wasn't my place to do that anyway.

170
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:44,870
I'll tell the master and everyone else

171
00:18:45,580 --> 00:18:48,960
that the young master
was the one who persuaded the king.

172
00:18:49,790 --> 00:18:51,000
That'll be great.

173
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:55,340
You can leave Arnheid's grave to me.

174
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:57,550
I will protect it.

175
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:05,260
Thank you so much.

176
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:07,720
It's nothing.

177
00:19:08,730 --> 00:19:13,150
Thorfinn, I want to become like you.

178
00:19:14,310 --> 00:19:15,650
I want to become

179
00:19:15,730 --> 00:19:20,530
a real man who is
strong and kind, like you.

180
00:19:25,370 --> 00:19:28,250
Olmar, I heard

181
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:32,290
that you made the decision to
stop fighting.

182
00:19:33,080 --> 00:19:34,670
That is a wonderful thing.

183
00:19:37,460 --> 00:19:41,260
It took me 15 years.

184
00:19:44,970 --> 00:19:46,260
But…

185
00:19:50,730 --> 00:19:54,940
I finally know what I am supposed to do.

186
00:19:56,940 --> 00:19:59,990
This is a wonderful farm.

187
00:20:01,150 --> 00:20:03,950
Please get it back on its feet
and protect it.

188
00:20:07,830 --> 00:20:09,120
Old master,

189
00:20:10,330 --> 00:20:11,790
thank you very much.

190
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:15,540
You always helped us out.

191
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:22,170
I told you,
it was just part of our contract.

192
00:20:22,760 --> 00:20:25,760
There is nothing for you to thank me for.

193
00:20:32,390 --> 00:20:36,560
I wish they took at least one silver mark.

194
00:20:45,610 --> 00:20:48,740
Thorfinn! Einar!

195
00:20:50,290 --> 00:20:55,920
My name is Roald! I am Roald, son of Grim!

196
00:21:02,170 --> 00:21:05,090
Thank you, Roald!

197
00:21:05,180 --> 00:21:07,550
I wish you all the best!

198
00:21:43,420 --> 00:21:44,460
Come here.

199
00:21:57,560 --> 00:21:59,350
Good boy.

200
00:22:00,190 --> 00:22:02,480
ENGRAVE IT

201
00:22:12,580 --> 00:22:17,370
ENGRAVE IT UPON YOUR BODY
ENGRAVE IT UPON THE LAND

202
00:22:23,710 --> 00:22:25,380
ENGRAVE IT UPON THE SEA

203
00:22:31,220 --> 00:22:35,770
ENGRAVE IT UPON YOUR LOOT
ENGRAVE IT UPON YOUR ENEMY

204
00:22:37,020 --> 00:22:38,310
ENGRAVE IT

205
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:45,070
Hey, when are you going to
start working, Boss?

206
00:22:45,150 --> 00:22:47,320
-Come on!
-Oh, quit yapping.

207
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:49,950
I was just taking a break.

208
00:22:50,030 --> 00:22:53,330
I'll show you how to really work a field.

209
00:22:53,410 --> 00:22:55,450
Oh, then why don't you show us?

210
00:22:56,790 --> 00:22:59,460
I'll finish this before you know it.

211
00:22:59,540 --> 00:23:02,710
ENGRAVE ITS TEXTURE UPON ME

212
00:23:16,930 --> 00:23:18,060
My life

213
00:23:19,850 --> 00:23:23,360
has always been about enduring,

214
00:23:24,560 --> 00:23:29,360
I thought the countless hardships
were part of living in this world.

215
00:23:35,330 --> 00:23:37,490
Would you have guessed that

216
00:23:37,580 --> 00:23:41,250
we would meet people
like those two, Arnheid?

217
00:23:45,540 --> 00:23:47,460
They're on their way…

218
00:23:50,050 --> 00:23:54,390
to a world that we can't even imagine.

219
00:23:57,600 --> 00:24:02,140
To a place other than here.

220
00:24:05,560 --> 00:24:12,530
ENGRAVE THAT ENCOUNTER UPON ME

221
00:25:53,840 --> 00:25:55,050
<i>"Hometown."</i>

222
00:25:55,130 --> 00:25:56,930
Subtitle translation by: Kiko Morita

